{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In the subsequent \"adaptive pruning\" phase, the server periodically adjusts the model by removing or reintroducing parameters over multiple iterations.",
    "FedPM [42] adopts a strategy inspired by the lottery ticket hypothesis for model pruning.",
    "Rather than utilizing a pruned model as an initial point, it initializes the random binary mask guided by the common seed for all clients.",
    "At the end of each round of FL training, clients return their binary masks to the server.",
    "The server then constructs a global model by computing a weighted average of these masks."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "FedPM [42] adopts a strategy inspired by the lottery ticket hypothesis for model pruning."
  ]
}